A C O N C U R R E N T R E S O L U T I O N
To urge Congress to make changes to the Fair Labor 1
Standards Act to allow a person under 16 years of age 2
to be employed between 7 p.m. and 9 p.m. during the 3
school year. 4
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE STATE OF OHIO (THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING):
WHEREAS, The United States lost over 22 million jobs and 5
had an unemployment rate of 14.8% in April 2020, as a result of 6
the COVID-19 pandemic, the highest observed unemployment rate 7
since data collection began in 1948; and 8
WHEREAS, Employers are still experiencing a shortage of 9
workers to fill the eight million currently available positions, 10
despite the economy recovering jobs that were lost because of 11
the COVID-19 pandemic; and 12
WHEREAS, Teenage workers are becoming a larger portion of 13
the United States workforce, with an unemployment rate of 13.2% 14
in November 2024; and 15
WHEREAS, Business owners have had to adjust their 16
operations in response to the ongoing labor shortage, including 17
decreasing their open hours; and 18

